CatDescriptText: Cutline for image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 14, 1973, p. 25, reads: "Summer Youth Sports Program Set - True Black Belt - Arie Foreman - Black Belt holder gives a demonstration of the techniques of Karate.  Arie right is the Coordinator of the program shows defensive methods."  Portion of accompanying article by Ben Wilson reads: "Once again, the University of Pittsburgh will be funded to conduct a National Summer Youth Sports  Program.  And in the past, the project at Pitt will be operated in conjunction with the Leisure-Learn Program.  The National Summer Youth Sports Program (NSYSP) is authorized, by and funded by, the United States Congress... - All Photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Young man performing karate move and Arie Foreman leaping
